Create an Einstein Segment in Data Cloud

Describe your segment to get suggested related attributes that are based on the data found in your org. To avoid bias and inaccuracies, all demographic attributes are removed. Attributes that produce fewer than 10 results for the segment population are also removed to improve the segment's accuracy.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To create a segment:	Data Cloud Admin or Data Cloud Marketing Admin
Available with add-on license: Segmentation and Activation

Some Data Cloud features have guidelines to optimize performance. Other features have restrictions or incur billing charges based on usage. Learn more about feature usage in the Data Cloud Limits and Guidelines.

Before you start building Einstein segments, review our recommendations on writing good prompts.

In Data Cloud, click Segments.
Click New.
Click Create with Einstein.
Select the Segment Properties.
Select the data space that the Unified Individual DMO that you’re basing this segment on is associated with.
From the Segment On dropdown, select the Unified Individual DMO that you’re basing your segment on.
Click Next.
In the Einstein Segment Creation chat, enter a segment description of at least two words using simple phrases, and then press Enter. After you enter a description, all the words are translated for you into attributes and values based on the data that exists in your org.
A segment description is created based on the phrase that you entered (1), and the attributes related to the description are created (2). For example, Einstein generative AI translates Canada into different values using the Residence Country Name attribute. The related attributes from other DMOs appear below the Unified Individual DMO attributes (3). For example, residence status, which relates to the country name appears under Demographics. Scroll down to view the attributes.
To edit the description or start over, click Refine Segment.
For an accurate population number, click Count Population. Counting takes time to complete. If you make changes to your segment draft, recount the population.
If you need to manually change any of the attributes or values this is done by clicking Edit Segment Rules. This action creates the segment and takes you to the Edit Rules tab. You can’t go back and make any changes in the editor afterwards. It’s recommended you do this only after you’re done creating your segment.
When you're satisfied with the segment and its attributes, click Create Segment.
What to do next: The new segment appears on the Segment list view. To use the segment, publish it.
